The paper deals with the analysis of Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) and their inner organization, which is a topic that falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes to analyze DNNs in the Information Plane, which is a concept from Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the optimization of the Information Bottleneck tradeoff, which is a topic in Neural Networks (cs.NE) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the unique mechanisms of Deep Neural Networks, which could be considered a topic in Systems and Control (cs.SI).
